  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>wedges</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheese-and-leek-glamorgan-style-patties-with-salad/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and finely chop</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>butter</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once melted, add the<strong> chopped leek </strong>and 30ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[45ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[60ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong>, then cook for 3 min or until the water has evaporated</p><p>Once evaporated, transfer the <strong>cooked leek </strong>onto a plate and leave to cool completely (reserve the pan for later!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheese-and-leek-glamorgan-style-patties-with-salad/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, separate the <strong>egg</strong> <strong>yolk[s] </strong>from the <strong>white[s]</strong> by cracking your <strong>egg </strong>over a shallow bowl and catching the <strong>yolk</strong> in the shell</p><p>Transfer the <strong>yolk</strong> from one shell half to the other several times, until all the <strong>whites</strong> are in the bowl and you are left with the yolk in the shell, then transfer the <strong>yolk</strong> to a separate shallow bowl</p><p>Grate your<strong> cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheese-and-leek-glamorgan-style-patties-with-salad/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into wedges, then peel and chop your <strong>red onion[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into wedges</p><p>After the potatoes have had their initial 15 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven and move the potatoes to one side</p><p>Add the<strong> tomato wedges </strong>and<strong> onion</strong> <strong>wedges</strong> and return the tray[s] to the oven for a further 15-20 min or until the potatoes have browned and crisped</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheese-and-leek-glamorgan-style-patties-with-salad/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine <strong>half</strong> of your<strong> panko breadcrumbs</strong> with the<strong> grated cheese</strong>, <strong>cooled</strong> <strong>leek</strong>, <strong>egg yolk</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>wholegrain mustard </strong>(save the rest for later!) – this is your <strong>patty mixture</strong></p><p>Season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then divide the mixture and shape into 1 patty per person</p><p>Gently coat the <strong>patties</strong> in the <strong>egg white</strong> and press them into the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>panko</strong> <strong>breadcrumbs </strong>– these are your <strong>Glamorgan-style patties</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheese-and-leek-glamorgan-style-patties-with-salad/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-low heat with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> Glamorgan-style patties </strong>and cook for 4-5 min on each side until browned and crispy, adding more <strong>vegetable oil </strong>if needed</p><p>Tip: Resist fiddling with the patties so they hold their shape!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheese-and-leek-glamorgan-style-patties-with-salad/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the patties are cooking, combine your <strong>mayo </strong>with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>wholegrain mustard </strong>(not a mustard fan? Go easy!), a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>wholegrain mayo</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> salad </strong>and pat it dry with kitchen paper, then combine with the <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>&</strong> <strong>onion</strong> – this is your<strong> roasted</strong> <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>&</strong> <strong>onion salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheese-and-leek-glamorgan-style-patties-with-salad/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dress the salad with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>Glamorgan-style patties</strong> with the <strong>potato wedges</strong>, <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>&</strong> <strong>onion salad </strong>and <strong>wholegrain mayo</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
